<!-- 
  SYNTHETIC UFDR — COORDINATED CRIMINAL NETWORK
  File: crime_network_syndicate.ufdr
  Purpose: Simulates a tightly-knit criminal group (6 members, hub-and-spoke topology)
           planning drug trafficking using encrypted comms, offshore coordination,
           and cryptocurrency payments.
  Use-case: Test graph-based network analysis, cross-device entity linking,
             and anomaly detection (foreign comms, late-night bursts, VPN tunnels).
-->
